    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.backpackinglight.dk/">Backpackinglight.dk</a> is another European ultralight shop which specializies in offering lightweight gear from across the world in one stop. As the name implies, they’re into ultralight backpacking - so can they take the lead in the <a href="http://hikinginfinland.com/blog/categories/one-stop-shop/">OSS</a>?</p>

<p><img style="max-width:100%" src="http://hendrikmorkel.github.com//cdn.thinglink.me/api/image/508171246194655232/1024/10/scaletowidth#tl-508171246194655232;1043138249" class="alwaysThinglink" /><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="http://hendrikmorkel.github.com//cdn.thinglink.me/jse/embed.js"></script></p>

<!-- more -->

<p><em>If you need to freshen up what this is all about, read the <a href="http://hikinginfinland.com/2014/03/one-stop-shop-introduction.html">Introduction</a>!</em></p>

<p><a href="http://www.backpackinglight.dk/">Backpackinglight.dk</a> exists since several years and like the <a href="http://hikinginfinland.com/2014/03/one-stop-shop-trekking-lite-store-dot-com.html">trekking-lite-store.com</a> offers European customers easy access to US cottages brands like Hyperlite Mountain Gear and ULA Equipment, besides some great European gear. However, they don’t have garments so again some items were included that come from other stores, in that case they’re marked with a *.</p>

